author: cmpilato
msg: Finish issue #1519 - 'svn up doesn't fetch modifications after
svn:externals URL has been changed'.
* subversion/libsvn_client/externals.c
(handle_external_item_change): For unchanged externals definitions,
we now check to see if the thing on disk matches the definition.  If
not, we re-checkout.

author: cmpilato
msg: * subversion/libsvn_fs/txn.c
(txn_body_abort_txn): Bail out immediately if someone is trying to
abort a committed Subversion transaction, instead of doing all the
work of cleaning up the Subversion transaction only to be denied
the removal the thing itself at the end of the function.  NOTE:
because we do all this cleanup in a single Berkeley transaction,
this is not a correctness fix -- a failure at Subversion
transaction time in the past would have resulted in none of the
cleanups "going live".  But what a waste of time...

author: maxb
msg: * tools/cvs2svn/run-tests.py: Update revision numbers to deal with extra empty
revision caused by the changes of r7253.

author: maxb
msg: Fix issue 1529.
* tools/cvs2svn/cvs2svn.py (Commit.commit): Do not erroneously special-case
deletion of cvs rev 1.1 - it is *not* a guarantee that there are no previous
revisions.
